description:
&lt;p&gt;Part Time 18.75 hours per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for a Specialist Speech and Language Therapist to cover Maternity Leave for a 12 month period within the Youth Offending Service covering the Swansea Bay Locality.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are a SBUHB employee you will first need to secure your line manager&#39;s permission before applying for this post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be working at a universal, targeted and specialist level supporting children and young people who are currently accessing the Youth Offending Service. You will also have the opportunity to deliver training and support to other members of staff within the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will join a small MDT, working in close collaboration with the local authority. There will be opportunities to network with other staff in education and health and to support the development of innovative service delivery options to engage children and young people with complex speech language and communication needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will also be part of the wider team of Speech &amp; Language Therapists working across the Health Board area to deliver Speech and Language Therapy in close cooperation with other professional colleagues.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We can offer you:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dedicated time and funding for appropriate CPD&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Active support for research, audit and evidence-based practice&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;SLT Total Team meetings and Paediatric SLT Team meetings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Professional and Clinical support from Highly Specialist Therapists within the SLT team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent resources&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Administrative support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ann MilliganClinical Lead SLT&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;01792 517863&lt;/p&gt;
